    "tags": {
      "source": "curated",
      "addedBy": "gap_fill",
      "notes": "246-foot (75m) refrigerator vessel based in St. Maarten, serviced Japanese fishing fleets. Deliberately set ablaze and cast adrift by owners in early 1981 when hurricane threatened St. Maarten harbor. Drifted toward Marina Cay; tugboat tow line snapped injuring crew member; sank 7.5 miles NW of Tortola. Lies on port side, starboard rail at ~15m (50ft), bottom at 23m (75ft). Three accessible cargo holds. Resident Goliath grouper documented. One confirmed whale shark encounter at site (Cuan Law dive). Note: some sources say built in Japan 1960 as Seujo Maru No. 1, but this is from a single source and unverified by second independent source.",
      "last_qa_date": "2026-05-20"
    }
  },
